race.comment: Like the chances of PATH TO PROFIT (13) who is having first run for the new yard. Former Maher-trained galloper who was a Mornington winner two back then midfield at Sandown. Looks well placed here and can kick off with a big run. I AM PIKI (9) is better than the form this campaign. Has since trialled nicely and will find this easier than last start. Has the claim and a low draw and will give a sight. REOFFER (16) was an Oakbank winner two back then rode the speed last time before fading. Has a low draw and the claim and is another who will give a sight. EFFUSIV (8) has been freshened since scoring at the provincials latest. Deserved the win and gets the claimer again. Tricky gate but has good speed and will be in this for a long way. ECLAIR VITALITY (17) ran on hard behind EFFUSIV latest and with the pace on up front will be steaming home late.
